rman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Judsonne Sr. was born in 1494, in Halifax, Yorkshire, England, his father, Timothy Judsonne, was 24 and his mother, Mrs Timothy Judsonne, was 23. He married Margaret Clarke in 1516, in Halifax, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1543, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1494–1543":"1494–1543","1496–Female":"1496–Surnud","1490–Female":"1490–Surnud","1515–1593":"1515–1593","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1472–Female":"1472–Surnud","1543":"1543","1496":"1496","1494":"1494","1472":"1472","1593":"1593","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1516":"1516","1515":"1515","England":"England","Halifax, Calderdale, Yorkshire, England":"Halifax, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Halifax, Yorkshire, England":"Halifax, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1494–1543":"1494–1543","1496–Female":"1496–Kuollut","1490–Female":"1490–Kuollut","1515–1593":"1515–1593","1470–Male":"1470–Kuollut","1472–Female":"1472–Kuollut","1543":"1543","1496":"1496","1494":"1494","1472":"1472","1593":"1593","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1516":"1516","1515":"1515","England":"England","Halifax, Calderdale, Yorkshire, England":"Halifax, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Halifax, Yorkshire, England":"Halifax, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1494–1543":"1494–1543","1496–Female":"1496–Décédée","1490–Female":"1490–Décédée","1515–1593":"1515–1593","1470–Male":"1470–Décédé","1472–Female":"1472–Décédée","1543":"1543","1496":"1496","1494":"1494","1472":"1472","1593":"